description:
In this episode, we follow John Calvin and his work in Geneva, Switzerland. Geneva would almost become a Protestant version of Rome, primarily through John Calvin's work on the Reformation. Many reformers would pass through this city in the 16th century from all over Europe, which is why John Calvin is often referred to as the 'International Reformer' as his influence spread far and wide.

To learn more about John Calvin visit our website to read our extended article about his life.
